  "text": "Configuration hot-reload patterns are implemented across both Kubernetes and Prometheus to enable dynamic configuration updates without process restarts.\n\n## Kubernetes Hot-Reload Patterns\n\nKubernetes implements hot-reload through file watching and atomic swaps:\n\n1. **File Watcher Infrastructure (pkg/util/filesystem/watcher.go)**: The WatchUntil() function provides the core file monitoring capability, combining fsnotify for event-driven watching with periodic polling as a fallback. This handles TOCTOU (time-of-check-time-of-use) race conditions and re-establishes watches after Remove/Rename events.\n\n2. **Authorization Config Reload (pkg/kubeapiserver/authorizer/reload.go)**: Demonstrates the complete hot-reload pattern. It watches the authorization config file, uses checkFile() to detect changes via bytes.Equal() and reflect.DeepEqual() comparisons, and atomically swaps the active authorizerResolver using atomic.Pointer[authorizerResolver] without dropping connections.\n\n3. **Dynamic Certificate/Key Management (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/dynamiccertificates/dynamic_serving_content.go)**: Hot-reloads TLS certificates using watchCertKeyFile() with fsnotify, validates certificates via loadCertKeyPair() before applying, and uses atomic.Value to swap active certificate pairs. The work queue pattern handles Remove/Rename events by re-establishing watches.\n\n4. **CA Bundle Reloading (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/dynamiccertificates/dynamic_cafile_content.go)**: Watches CA files using fsnotify, checks if CA changed with hasCAChanged() using bytes.Equal(), and atomically updates the CA bundle without disrupting client authentication.\n\n5. **Encryption Config Controller (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/options/encryptionconfig/controller/controller.go)**: Uses polling-based reload (PollUntilContextCancel with configurable interval) instead of fsnotify, checks file hash, and includes double-check TOCTOU prevention in processEncryptionConfig() before applying transformers.\n\n6. **Kubelet File Watcher (pkg/kubelet/config/file.go)**: Monitors pod manifest files via fsnotify with periodic polling fallback, converts filesystem events to pod updates, and handles backoff retry strategies.\n\n## Prometheus Hot-Reload Patterns\n\nPrometheus implements hot-reload through signal handlers, checksums, and coordinated subsystem reloads:\n\n1. **Configuration Reload Orchestration (cmd/prometheus/main.go)**: The reloadConfig() function is the central hot-reload orchestrator triggered by three mechanisms: SIGHUP signal handler, HTTP API endpoint, and automatic periodic polling. It uses configuration change detection before triggering subsystem reloads and records reload metrics (prometheus_config_last_reload_successful).\n\n2. **Config Diff Detection (config/reload.go)**: The GenerateChecksum() function implements lightweight change detection using SHA256 hashing of the config file plus all referenced external files (rule_files, scrape_config_files). This enables periodic polling without expensive config parsing.\n\n3. **Scrape Pool Reload (scrape/manager.go)**: The ApplyConfig() function atomically reloads scrape targets using reflect.DeepEqual() for config diff detection. It manages concurrent pool updates through a buffered triggerReload channel and performs atomic pool swaps in the scrapePools map with deferred cleanup of old pools.\n\n4. **Alertmanager Config Reload (notifier/manager.go)**: ApplyConfig() uses hash-based comparison for alertmanager sets and atomically swaps alert target sets while reusing compatible resources and deferring cleanup of obsolete configurations.\n\n5. **Discovery Manager Reload (discovery/manager.go)**: ApplyConfig() manages service discovery providers concurrently, canceling obsolete providers while registering new ones without interrupting existing target discovery.\n\n6. **File-Based Service Discovery (discovery/file/file.go)**: Implements event-driven discovery using fsnotify.Watcher with watchFiles() establishing watches on discovery files. Falls back to periodic ticker-based refresh on watcher failures and properly drains events during graceful shutdown.\n\n7. **Alert Rules Reload (rules/manager.go)**: The Update() function dynamically reloads alert rule files during config reload without process restart.\n\n8. **HTTP Reload Endpoint (web/web.go)**: The Reload() function exposes an HTTP API for triggering configuration reloads independent of signals, returning channels for async request handling.\n\n## Common Hot-Reload Patterns\n\nBoth Kubernetes and Prometheus share architectural patterns for zero-downtime configuration updates:\n\n- **File Watching**: fsnotify for event-driven monitoring with periodic polling fallback for reliability\n- **Change Detection**: Byte-level equality checks (bytes.Equal) for files, hash comparison (SHA256) for periodic polling, and reflect.DeepEqual for structured config objects\n- **Atomic Swaps**: atomic.Pointer and atomic.Value provide thread-safe configuration transitions without locks\n- **Work Queues**: Rate-limited queues handle reload events with backoff retry logic\n- **Concurrent Reload**: Independent subsystems reload concurrently via goroutines and buffered channels\n- **Graceful Degradation**: Failed reloads don't affect current state; old resources are deferred cleanup\n- **No Connection Drop**: Existing client/target connections are maintained across configuration updates\n"
}

